# Defect Lifecycle

## Purpose
Defines the full lifecycle of a defect from discovery to closure to ensure
clear communication, prioritization and resolution flow.

## Defect Status Flow
New → Open → Assigned → In Progress → Fixed → Retest → Verified → Closed

## Possible Additional States
- Rejected
- Deferred / Postponed
- Duplicate
- Cannot Reproduce

## Priority Levels
P1 – Critical  
P2 – High  
P3 – Medium  
P4 – Low

## Severity Levels
S1 – System crash / data loss  
S2 – Major functionality broken  
S3 – Minor impact  
S4 – Cosmetic / UI

## Closure Criteria
- Fix verified
- No regression impact
- Approved by QA
